main_00-05#f#.description:

tr_06.description: Learn about the synergy between Defender Operators and AoE Caster Operators.

main_00-08.description: Swarms of Originium Slugs are approaching from 9 o'clock. It's recommended to deploy AoE Caster Operators.

main_00-08#f#.description:

main_00-09.description: More enemy Originium Slugs and shielded soldiers have arrived on the battlefield. Use a combination of Defender Operators and AoE Caster Operators to suppress them.

tr_07.name: Combat Skills
tr_07.description: Learn how to use Skills and how to take on strong enemies with Defender Operators.

main_00-10.name: Dilemma
main_00-10.description: Enemy Junkmen have high HP and ATK. Please deploy Defender Operators to block them, and deploy high-damage Operators to defeat them.

main_00-10#f#.name: Dilemma
main_00-10#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DEF of all ally units is halved.

main_00-11#f#.name: Blockade Running
main_00-11#f#.description:

main_01-01.name: Isolated Island
main_01-01.description:
The battlefield is narrower than before, and the enemies have gotten stronger.
Please make sure your Operators have been upgraded before entering the battlefield.

main_01-01#f#.name: Isolated Island
main_01-01#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The deployment limit is reduced to 4.

main_01-02.name: Sprawl
main_01-02.description:
At the same time, members of the Op Reserve Team have run into new enemies on their way to help... Please pay attention to the surprise attack from the north.
<@lv.item><Fixed Squad></> Unable to edit the squad

main_01-03.name: Running Wild
main_01-03.description:
This battlefield is wider and enemies will attack from two paths.
Please note that enemies coming from the southern path have higher defense. Think carefully about where to deploy your Operators.

main_01-03#f#.name: Running Wild
main_01-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of enemy units is increased significantly

main_01-04.name: Omen
main_01-04.description: The battlefield is even wider this time. You will need at least 3 melee Operators to block all the enemies.

main_01-04#f#.name: Omen
main_01-04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The cost of all ranged Operators is tripled

main_01-05.name: Paralysis
main_01-05.description: This battle takes place on Chernobog's main street. Please have at least 4 melee Operators in the squad to block all the enemies.

main_01-05#f#.name: Paralysis
main_01-05#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Speed of enemy units is increased significantly

main_01-06.name: Catastrophe
main_01-06.description:
Roadblocks help us control enemy movements when they approach from multiple directions. 
Please deploy Roadblocks to control the flow of battle. 
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block a tile on the map. Enemies will attack it if no path is available.

main_01-06#f#.name: Catastrophe
main_01-06#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The number of available Roadblocks is reduced to 1

tr_09.name: Indirect Protection
tr_09.description: Learn to take advantage of whatever may be available on the battlefield.

main_01-07.name: Tyrant
main_01-07.description:
Please combine your Operators' firepower with the Stun Generator on the battlefield to stop the enemy attack.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

main_01-07#f#.name: Tyrant
main_01-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Deployment Points recover at half the normal rate.

main_01-08.name: Resolve
main_01-08.description:
Be careful of the large number of approaching enemies, but keep an eye on the agile Reunion leader.
The Stun Generator can stop her movement for a short time.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

main_01-08#f#.name: Resolve
main_01-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The CD time of the enemy leader's ability is reduced significantly.

tr_10.name: Squad Defense
tr_10.description: Learn how to protect weak Operators with the deployment order.

main_01-09.name: Rout
main_01-09.description:
Enemies won't slow down their attack even during a Catastrophe.
Please pay attention to enemy ranged units and protect your own ranged Operators.

main_01-10.name: Remnants
main_01-10.description:
We are not far from the outskirts of Chernobog. Hang in there and victory will be ours.
Please pay attention to enemy ranged units and protect your own ranged Operators.

main_01-10#f#.name: Remnants
main_01-10#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enemy ranged units have significantly increased range.

main_01-11.name: The Forgotten
main_01-11.description:
At the same time, Op Reserve Team members have run into W, one of the enemy's leaders, on their way to help... Observe W's movements carefully while defending against the enemy attack.
<@lv.item><Fixed Squad></> Unable to edit the squad

main_01-12.name: Pyrrhic Victory
main_01-12.description:
W's troops have launched their attack from Chernobog's labyrinthine streets. Make good use of the environment.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

main_01-12#f#.name: Pyrrhic Victory
main_01-12#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The cost of Medic Operators is doubled.

tr_11.name: Tactical Blockage
tr_11.description: Learn to use Supports and Caster Operators to take on the enemy's armored units.

main_02-01.name: To Lungmen
main_02-01.description: The paths on the battlefield are tortuous. Consider using Supports to suppress the enemy's elite units.

sub_02-01.name: Slow-1
sub_02-01.description: Please pay attention to the enemy's shielded soldiers, who have high defense.

main_02-02.name: War of Words
main_02-02.description: More enemies with high defense have appeared in the center of the battlefield. Support and Caster Operators can reduce their combat power significantly.

sub_02-02.name: Slow-2
sub_02-02.description: Please pay attention to the aerial units to the north and south.

sub_02-03.name: Blockade-1
sub_02-03.description:
Deploy Roadblocks in the right places to stop enemies advancing from two directions.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance

sub_02-04.name: Blockade-2
sub_02-04.description:
The battlefield is even more complicated now. Think carefully before deploying the Roadblocks.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance

main_02-03.name: Presumption of Innocence
main_02-03.description:
Enemies are coming from too many directions this time, complicating your deployment.
Use Roadblocks to control the enemy's advance.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance.

main_02-03#f#.name: Presumption of Innocence
main_02-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The cost of Roadblocks and melee Operators is doubled

tr_12.name: Casters
tr_12.description: Learn how to reduce the damage taken from enemy AOE units by deploying Operators in formation.

main_02-04.description:
Enemy Elite Casters confirmed.
This type of enemy can pose a huge threat to your Operators. Scatter them.

main_02-04#f#.name: Penguin Logistics
main_02-04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of enemy units is increased significantly

sub_02-05.name: Caster-1
sub_02-05.description: The enemy's Elite Casters have scattered. Protocol advises taking them out one by one with Sniper Operators.

sub_02-06.name: Caster-2
sub_02-06.description: The enemy's Elite Casters remain the biggest threat. Scatter your Operators to reduce damage taken.

sub_02-07.name: Caster-3
sub_02-07.description: The enemy has sent even more Elite Casters. Scatter the Operators as previous.

tr_13.name: Proactive Deployment
tr_13.description: Learn to intercept the enemy's key units with Operators.

main_02-05.name: Falling Objects
main_02-05.description:
Massive deployment of enemy Elite Casters confirmed.
Protocol advises destroying them one by one.

main_02-05#f#.name: Falling Objects
main_02-05#f#.description:

The cost of Guard and Sniper Operators is doubled

main_02-06.name: Hold on Tight
main_02-06.description:
The roof is wide enough to deploy a variety of formations.
Still, watch out for surprise attacks...

tr_14.name: Terrain Attack
tr_14.description: Learn to destroy tough enemies using the environment.

main_02-07.name: A Matter of Public Health
main_02-07.description: Enemy's new aerial units have been confirmed on your 1 o'clock and 7 o'clock. Please exercise caution.

main_02-07#f#.description:

The range of enemy's ranged units is increased significantly

sub_02-08.description: The roof is not surrounded by railings. Make good use of that and things will be much easier.

sub_02-09.name: Trap-2
sub_02-09.description: Enemies have become stronger. Using the terrain is still the key to victory.

main_02-08.name: No Promises
main_02-08.description:
Some vantage points on the roof are ideal for sniping the enemy's aerial units.
Also, the roof is not surrounded by railings. Can we use that to our advantage...?
<@lv.item><Anti-air Rune></> Operators deployed on it will attack a bit more slowly but their ATK against aerial units will be increased significantly

main_02-08#f#.name: No Promises
main_02-08#f#.description:

The weight of enemy units is increased significantly

main_02-09.name: Cubiculum Obscurum
main_02-09.description:
The battlefield is narrow this time. Please make sure you have enough melee Operators to stop enemies.
<@lv.item><Anti-air Rune></> Operators deployed on it will attack a bit more slowly but their ATK against aerial units will be increased significantly

main_02-09#f#.name: Cubiculum Obscurum
main_02-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of enemy units is increased significantly

sub_02-10.description: Please pay attention to the surprise attack from the south.

sub_02-11.name: Suffocation-2
sub_02-11.description: The battlefield is completely divided again. Try to defend against enemies from both directions.

sub_02-12.name: Suffocation-3
sub_02-12.description: Please pay attention to the surprise attack launched by enemy aerial units from the east and west.

main_02-10.name: Beyond Cure
main_02-10.description:
Skullshatterer attacks with her troops! This complicated battlefield will be a test of your skills.

main_02-10#f#.description:

main_03-01.description:
When fighting in the wild, Operators can take cover in some forms of terrain to reduce damage taken, but please pay attention to the enemy's invisible troops.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

main_03-01#f#.name: Meeting
main_03-01#f#.description:

main_03-02.description:
The enemy has sent even more ranged units.
Eliminate them first as they pose a greater threat.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

main_03-02#f#.name: Memory
main_03-02#f#.description:

main_03-03.description:
Enemies equipped with a Detector can disable the effect of Bushes.
Be aware of the enemy leader, who has the ability to disrupt our formation.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

main_03-03#f#.name: Convolution
main_03-03#f#.description:

The weight of enemy units is increased by 1 level

tr_15.description: Learn to retreat Operators in time to pass the final test.

An previously unknown enemy leader and an elite team are launching a ferocious attack from 6 o'clock.
Deploy operators to engage immediately!
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

main_03-04#f#.description:

main_03-05.description:
Enemy's Invisible Casters have been confirmed on the battlefield.
Eliminate them first as they pose a greater threat.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

main_03-05#f#.name: Call
main_03-05#f#.description:

main_03-06.name: Decision
main_03-06.description:
The enemy has deployed many invisible ranged units.
Use the Detector to launch a counterattack.
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will reveal nearby invisible enemies for a peroid of time.

main_03-07.name: Roar
main_03-07.description:
The battlefield is complicated. Use Roadblocks to guide enemies into range of our Snipers.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></>Deploy it to block the enemy's advance
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will reveal nearby invisible enemies for a period of time.

main_03-07#f#.name: Roar
main_03-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The number of available Roadblocks is reduced to 2

main_03-08.name: Dusk
main_03-08.description:
Skullshatterer is coming at us with her troops again, only more dangerous...
<@lv.item><Defense Rune></> Operators deployed on it will have higher DEF

main_03-08#f#.name: Dusk
main_03-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of enemy units is increased significantly

main_04-01#f#.description:

The range of enemy's ranged units is increased significantly

main_04-02.description:
Ranged soldiers of another race have joined the battle.
Protocol advises deploying physical Operators to counter them.

main_04-02#f#.name: A Walk in the Rain
main_04-02#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DEF of all ally units is halved.

main_04-03.description:
High-energy Originium radiation has been detected in Chernobog.
If enemy units absorb this radiation...
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly.

main_04-03#f#.name: Artificial Cold
main_04-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The ATK of enemy units is increased significantly.

main_04-04.name: Nerves of Steel
main_04-04.description:
The enemy has launched their final attack and approaches from all directions! Deploy Operators to repel them immediately.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></>Deploy it to block the enemy's advance.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly.

main_04-04#f#.name: Nerves of Steel
main_04-04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Speed of enemy units is increased significantly

main_04-05.name: Bureaucracy
main_04-05.description: Enemy melee Arts units have been confirmed on the battlefield. Avoid engaging in melee combat with them. Stay alert.

main_04-05#f#.name: Bureaucracy
main_04-05#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of all melee Operators is halved

main_04-06.description:
Unknown creatures infected with Oripathy have been found on the battlefield. They deal massive damage to nearby Operators when they die.
In addition, please look out for Heated Paths. They emit burning gas.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

main_04-07.name: Mutual Benefits
main_04-07.description:
A large number of creatures infected with Oripathy have appeared on the battlefield!
Think carefully about when to destroy them.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

main_04-07#f#.name: Mutual Benefits
main_04-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The explosive damage dealt by enemy units is increased significantly

main_04-08.name: Acute Stress Disorder
main_04-08.description: A force of mixed enemy troops advances on us from the east. Prepare to engage.

main_04-08#f#.name: Acute Stress Disorder
main_04-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The redeployment time of all Operators is doubled

main_04-09.name: Bad to the Bone
main_04-09.description:
Enemy Elite Casters of another race have been confirmed on the battlefield.
They seem to have special powers. Please be careful.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

main_04-09#f#.name: Bad to the Bone
main_04-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DEF of enemy units is increased significantly

main_04-10.name: Extinguished Flames
main_04-10.description:
FrostNova and her elite team have the area completely surrounded.
All we can do now is to engage and hold them at our perimeter.

main_04-10#f#.name: Extinguished Flames
main_04-10#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The ATK and Skill range of FrostNova are increased significantly

main_05-01.name: Cycle of Enmity
main_05-01.description: Enemy units have been spotted in the wilds outside Lungmen. Beware of the swift moving Breakers and well-protected Spec Ops Casters in particular.

main_05-01#f#.name: Cycle of Enmity
main_05-01#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The ATK of all friendly melee units is reduced by 50%

main_05-02.name: Inexpressible
main_05-02.description: A large number of Reunion forces have been spotted in urbanized areas of Lungmen. Beware of Breakers approaching from 12 o'clock.

main_05-02#f#.name: Inexpressible
main_05-02#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Attack Speed of enemy units is increased significantly

main_05-03.name: Courage and Mortality
main_05-03.description: Enemy Spec Ops Caster Leaders have spread throughout the battlefield. They can break our operators in an instant without proper preparation against their Arts attacks. Plan carefully.

main_05-03#f#.name: Courage and Mortality
main_05-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The range of enemy's ranged units is increased significantly

main_05-04.name: Nobody’s Home
main_05-04.description: A swarm of enemy drones approaches from 4 directions. Beware of a new type of enemy drone, the bomb-carrying Bombtails.

main_05-04#f#.name: Nobody’s Home
main_05-04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Speed of enemy units is increased significantly

main_05-05.name: Unending War
main_05-05.description: An enhanced version of the enemy Bombtail drone has entered the battle. Their AOE damaging explosive bombs can make quick work of our defensive line. Do what you can to counter them beforehand.

main_05-05#f#.name: Unending War
main_05-05#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The redeployment time of all Operators is doubled

main_05-06.name: Surprise Attack
main_05-06.description:
The enemy's Arts Master drones are highly maneuverable and capable of launching Arts attacks from above. Counter them with our newly developed Drone Jammer. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

main_05-06#f#.name: Surprise Attack
main_05-06#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The cost of the Jammer is doubled

main_05-07.description:
Frost Drones greatly reduce the Attack Speed of our nearby units. Counter them with operators or Jammers to prevent them from using their abilities. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

main_05-07#f#.name: In Life and in Death
main_05-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Sniper and Caster Operators may not be deployed.

main_05-08.name: Intimate Knowledge
main_05-08.description:
A group of strange enemy soldiers with regeneration abilities have arrived on the battlefield. Eliminate them as quickly as possible. Arrange your deployment to avoid enemy Turrets. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

main_05-08#f#.name: Intimate Knowledge
main_05-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DEF of enemy units is increased significantly

main_05-09.name: The Devil
main_05-09.description:
Things just keep getting stranger... Enemy Veteran Junkmen now have regenerative abilities as well. Take care to eliminate them as quickly as possible. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

main_05-09#f#.name: The Devil
main_05-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The HP of enemy units is increased significantly

main_05-10.name: The Dark Before Dawn
main_05-10.description:
We are now deep behind enemy lines and there is no going back. Use your tactical expertise and find a way through the crossfire between Mephisto and Faust! 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

main_05-10#f#.name: The Dark Before Dawn
main_05-10#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Mephisto's HP and DEF are greatly increased

st_05-01.name: Decisive Counterattack
st_05-01.description: Victories are short, but wars are long, and our enemies are unknown.

sub_03-1-1.name: Lurking-1
sub_03-1-1.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's invisible units and Casters.

sub_03-1-2.name: Lurking-2
sub_03-1-2.description: Enemy only focuses their attack on one spot, but still it's recommended to deploy Operators in the rear.

sub_03-2-1.name: Recon-1
sub_03-2-1.description:
Making good use of the Bushes and the Detector is the key to victory.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will disable the invisibility of nearby enemies for a certain period

sub_03-2-2.name: Recon-2
sub_03-2-2.description:
Enemies are attacking from different routes this time. Please make sure you have enough melee Operators to stop them.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack

sub_03-2-3.name: Recon-3
sub_03-2-3.description: The route is simple this time. It will be a test for your Operators' strength.

sub_04-1-1.name: Cluster-1
sub_04-1-1.description:
Make good use of the Active Originium in the middle of the battlefield and things will be much easier.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-2.name: Cluster-2
sub_04-1-2.description:
Enemies are coming from more directions. Still it's recommended to build your defense around the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-3.description:
The alien force has split into two. It may be a good choice to consume their HP by the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-2-1.name: Myriapoda-1
sub_04-2-1.description: Please be careful of the Originium Slugs in the south and the north and don't let them go through our defense.

sub_04-2-2.name: Myriapoda-2
sub_04-2-2.description: The battlefield is narrow this time. Please think carefully about where to deploy Operators.

sub_04-2-3.name: Myriapoda-3
sub_04-2-3.description: The battlefield is even narrower. It's recommended to upgrade Operators to get through it.

sub_04-3-1.name: Rage-1
sub_04-3-1.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's Originium Slugs and alien elite Casters.

sub_04-3-2.name: Rage-2
sub_04-3-2.description: Scatter the Operators and use ranged Operators to take out the Originium Slugs from afar.

sub_04-3-3.name: Rage-3
sub_04-3-3.description: There is not much space for melee Operators this time. Try using Specialist Operators to cope with the tough enemies on the left.

sub_05-1-1.name: Entrenched-1
sub_05-1-1.description: The enemies continue their massed assault. Beware of the Wraiths sneaking in from above.

sub_05-1-2.name: Entrenched-2
sub_05-1-2.description: The situation in the field is getting more complicated. Carefully deploy melee Operators to stop the swarm of enemy Breakers.

sub_05-2-1.name: Biting Cold-1
sub_05-2-1.description: Well armored Frost Drones are causing havoc with our forces. Counter them with Caster Operators.

sub_05-2-2.name: Biting Cold-2
sub_05-2-2.description:
The enemy force is a mix of Arts Masters and Frost Drones making it increasingly difficult to handle. Make use of Sniper and Caster Operators and don't forget our Jammers! 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

sub_05-3-1.name: Panic-1
sub_05-3-1.description:
Possessed Soldier Leaders can regenerate faster and pose a serious threat. Take them out first. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

sub_05-3-2.name: Panic-2
sub_05-3-2.description:
Defense Crushers are enemy elite units specialized in defense. Their attacks can also stun our melee units. Take advantage of their slow moving speed to counter them. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

hard_05-01.name: Operation Inferno-1
hard_05-01.description:
The enemy is attacking with the full force of their drone armada! Proper use of Snipers and Casters is the key to victory. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

hard_05-02.name: Operation Inferno-2
hard_05-02.description: The terrain on this battlefield is relatively simple, but beware of enemy Casters. Consider deploying units with high Arts Res to draw their fire fire or take advantage of the holes on the ground.

hard_05-03.name: Operation Inferno-3
hard_05-03.description:
The battlefield is full of winding roads and blanketed in a poisonous haze. These factors have greatly hindered our ranged Operators' effectiveness. Consider deploying more Medic Operators maintain consistent healing. 
<@lv.item><Poison Haze></> Operators lose HP constantly

hard_05-04.name: Operation Inferno-4
hard_05-04.description:
Faust has returned even stronger than before, and all Turrets on the field have been greatly enhanced. Plan your deployment positions and operators carefully to repel Faust's ferocious attack! 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

pro_a_1.description:
A mission to acquire the materials needed for the Promotion of Defender and Medic Operators.
The battle will be easier if you employ Defender and Medic Operators well.
<@lv.item><Poison Haze></> Operators lose HP constantly.

a001_01.name: High Noon
a001_01.description:
Sand is blowing wildly outside Kazimierz. Down from the abandoned gallows there is a greedy, cunning rioter, while behind him stands a knight who has just crossed the desert alone with nothing but the lance in her hand.
<@lv.rem>Some Operators cannot be deployed</>

a001_02.name: Sophistication
a001_02.description: People gather in the bar for all sorts of different reasons. They each have their own axe to grind, but after weighing the pros and cons, decide to work together over a few rounds of beer. However, before they can even take two steps out the door, the temporary truce falls apart violently. Such is the life of bounty hunters.

a001_03.name: An Unexpected Journey
a001_03.description:
Nobody is going to give up the treasure without a fight, and the troublemakers just keep coming one after another. Obviously, most of them have no idea what a "fair fight" means.
<@lv.rem>Some Operators cannot be deployed</>

a001_04.name: Turn State’s Evidence
a001_04.description:
Even more reliable than death and taxes is the unpredictability of life. It even works on your friends, your enemies, and even your own beliefs.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.

a001_05.name: Different Opinions
a001_05.description:
It’s said that no great fortune comes without sin, because the path to wealth is always paved with violence and bloodshed.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.

a001_06.name: Golden Triangle
a001_06.description:
Everyone has their own path. You choose your path, while she chooses hers. Some roads may be more dangerous than others, but we all reach the same destination in the end.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.

a001_ex01.name: True Grit
a001_ex01.description: These little critters that have crawled up from underground are extremely dangerous. Their homes have been destroyed as a result of the bounty hunters’ rampant excavation, so all they know how to do now is to return the favor.

a001_ex02.name: No Country for Old Men
a001_ex02.description: The terrain is simple but the fighting is gritty. Useless traps and coins are scattered everywhere.

a001_ex04.name: The Treasure of the Kazimierz Mortica
a001_ex04.description:
It's annoying to dig for treasure underground, because you can never tell whether it's dirt or an Originium Slug that falls into your hair.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.

a001_ex04#f#.name: The Treasure of the Kazimierz Mortica
a001_ex04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The deployment cost of ranged Operators is tripled.

a001_ex05.name: Stagecoach
a001_ex05.description:
To seize victory, one must carve a bloody path through the defenses of their enemies. Our poor enemies.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.

a001_ex05#f#.name: Stagecoach
a001_ex05#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Attack Speed of all enemies is increased significantly

a001_ex06.name: Once Upon a Time in the West
a001_ex06.description:
Heavily armed enemies are constantly pouring in from all directions. It’s not their fault — you blocked the only way out, after all.
<@lv.item><Eroded Path></> Operators deployed on these tiles have their DEF reduced by half.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block the enemy's route

a001_ex06#f#.name: Once Upon a Time in the West
a001_ex06#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The cost of Roadblocks is tripled

camp_01.name: Chernobog
camp_01.description:
Annihilate the large number of Reunion mobs in Chernobog. Watch out for the leaders who patrol the area.
<@lv.rem><Condition></> Deployment Points will not automatically recover.

camp_02.name: Lungmen: Outskirts
camp_02.description:
The Reunion terrorists are hiding on the outskirts of Lungmen. Annihilate them to protect Lungmen from any threats.
<@lv.rem><Condition></> Deployment Points will not automatically recover.

camp_03.name: Lungmen: Downtown
camp_03.description:
Annihilate the Reunion forces in urban Lungmen and take back the initiative in this region. 
<@lv.rem><Condition></> Deployment Points will not automatically recover.

tile_bigforce.name: Specialist Tactical Point
tile_bigforce.description: Increases the push and pull strength of the Operator on it.

tile_corrosion.name: Corrosive Ground
tile_corrosion.description: Reduces DEF by half of the Operator on it.

tile_deepwater.name: Deep Water Zone
tile_deepwater.description: Represents the water terrain far from the shore

tile_def.name: Defensive Rune
tile_def.description: Increases DEF of the Operator on it.

tile_end.name: Protection Objective
tile_end.description: Blue objective point. Its HP decreases when an enemy unit enters it.

tile_fence.name: Fence
tile_fence.description: Can deploy melee unit on it. Impassable

tile_floor.name: Non-deployable Area
tile_floor.description: Can't deploy melee unit on it. Passable

tile_flystart.name: Aerial Unit Incursion Point
tile_flystart.description: Enemy aerial units will enter the battlefield from here.

tile_forbidden.name: No Entry Zone
tile_forbidden.description: Can't deploy melee unit on it. Impassable

tile_gazebo.name: Anti-Air Rune
tile_gazebo.description: Slightly reduces ASPD but greatly increases ATK against aerial units of the Operator on it.

tile_grass.name: Bush
tile_grass.description: The Operator on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

tile_healing.name: Medical Rune
tile_healing.description: The Operator on it will recover HP over time.

tile_hole.name: Hole
tile_hole.description: A dangerous hole in the ground. Enemies that step on it will fall to their deaths.

tile_infection.name: Active Originium
tile_infection.description: Increases ATK and ASPD of both friendly and enemy units that stand on it, but the affected units will lose HP over time.

tile_rcm_crate.name: Recommended Roadblock Point
tile_rcm_crate.description: A recommended location to deploy Roadblocks by PRTS.

tile_rcm_operator.name: Recommended Deployment Point
tile_rcm_operator.description: A recommended location to deploy units by PRTS.

tile_road.name: Flat Ground
tile_road.description: Can deploy melee unit on it. Passable

tile_shallowwater.name: Shallow Water Zone
tile_shallowwater.description: Represents the water terrain by the shore

tile_start.name: Incursion Point
tile_start.description: Enemies will enter the battlefield from here.

tile_telin.name: Tunnel Entry
tile_telin.description: Enemies will enter the tunnel from here and appear from where it leads to.

tile_telout.name: Tunnel Exit
tile_telout.description: Enemies that have entered the tunnel will reappear from here.

tile_volcano.name: Heat Pump Passage
tile_volcano.description: Pumps out high temperature gas periodically, dealing damage that ignores DEF and Art Res to any units on it.

tile_volspread.name: Lava Crack
tile_volspread.description: Spray out lava periodically, dealing massive damage to friendly units on the surrounding 8 tiles and melting down Roadblocks.

tile_wall.name: High Ground
tile_wall.description: Can deploy ranged unit on it. Impassable
